<h3>During the Month of October 2012,<br>We will Pray for our Families, Churches, <br>Government, Schools, &amp; the 2012 Election.</h3><blockquote>"If my people who, who are called by my name, will humble themselves and pray and seek my face and turn from their wicked ways, then I will hear from heaven and will forgive their sin and will heal their land."<strong>&nbsp;-2 Chronicles 7:14 (God speaking to King Solomon)</strong></blockquote><h4><img src="http://www.pcctoday.com/monkimage.php?mediaDirectory=mediafiles&amp;mediaId=1752399&amp;fileName=graphic--31-days-of-prayer--devotion-icon-0-0-120-120.jpg" width="120" height="120" alt="GRAPHIC : 31 Days of Prayer : Devotion Icon - 31 Days of Prayer Devotional" title="GRAPHIC : 31 Days of Prayer : Devotion Icon - 31 Days of Prayer Devotional" style="float: left;">Month Of Prayer<br>October 1 - 31&nbsp;</h4><p>Throughout October, Pastor Ray is calling our church to pray for our nation. Each day the guide will direct you to <strong>pray for a different area of government or national concern</strong> along with highlighting a quote from one of our founding fathers, a scripture passage, a reflection with discussion questions, and a prayer. Read this on your own or involve the entire family. We will be posting daily on facebook &amp; PCCToday.com. Please <a href="#prayerguide"><strong>click here</strong></a> to see a full listing of the 31 Days of Prayer Articles.&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><h4><img src="http://www.pcctoday.com/monkimage.php?mediaDirectory=mediafiles&amp;mediaId=1752407&amp;fileName=graphic--31-days-of-prayer--week-of-fasting-icon-0-0-120-120.jpg" width="120" height="120" alt="GRAPHIC : 31 Days of Prayer : Week of Fasting Icon - One Week of Fasting" title="GRAPHIC : 31 Days of Prayer : Week of Fasting Icon - One Week of Fasting" style="float: left;"><strong>Week of Fasting &amp; Prayer<br>October 28 - November 4&nbsp;</strong></h4><p><strong></strong>To end this amazing month of prayer we invite you to join you Portland Christian Center family in a<strong> seven day fast</strong>. We will begin fasting Monday Morning, October 29th and will break our fast Sunday night November 4th after our second Community Prayer Night. During this week we invite you to fast in several different ways. The important point of fasting being replacing whatever activity you deny yourself for that seven days with prayer and meditation on God. <strong>Fore more information abour different ways to fast please visit our fasting help page located by</strong> <a href="/fasting/"><strong>clicking here</strong>.</a></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;</p><h4><img src="http://www.pcctoday.com/monkimage.php?mediaDirectory=mediafiles&amp;mediaId=1752403&amp;fileName=graphic--31-days-of-prayer--community-prayer-night-icon-0-0-120-120.jpg" width="120" height="120" alt="GRAPHIC : 31 Days of Prayer : Community Prayer Night Icon - Two Community Prayer Nights" title="GRAPHIC : 31 Days of Prayer : Community Prayer Night Icon - Two Community Prayer Nights" style="float: left;">Two Community Prayer Nights&nbsp;<br>September 30 &amp; November 4</h4><p>Join your your church family for two community prayer nights. As the body of Christ we will come together to praise God for his faithfulness, ask him in humility to bless our families, friends, neighborhoods, schools, local government &amp; federal government. We will also bring the 2012 election before the throne of God. These two nights of prayer and worship are based on the verse 2 Chronicles 7:14</p><p>&nbsp;</p><h3><a name="prayerguide"></a>Praying for Our Nation&nbsp;<br>31 Days of Prayer Devotional and Prayer Guide</h3><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Each day from October 1 - 31 we will be posting the articles found our free prayer guide, "Praying for Our Nation and Families." You can follow along through the links below, or you can pick up a beautiful paper copy in the lobby beginning Sunday September 23, 2012. This prayer guide is designed to help you begin to pray hopefully and expectantly for God to heal and transform our nation and families for the glory of God. Just click on the links below to access the devotional for that day.</p><ul><li><a href="/article/introduction-to-the-31-days-of-prayer/">Introduction</a></li><li><a href="/article/day-1-devotional-praying-for-our-president/">October 1 - Day 1&nbsp;</a>&nbsp;</li><li><a href="/article/day-2-devotional-praying-for-our-vice-president/">October 2 -&nbsp;Day 2</a>&nbsp;</li><li><a href="/article/day-3-devotional-praying-for-our-supreme-court/">October 3 -&nbsp;Day 3</a><img src="http://www.pcctoday.com/monkimage.php?mediaDirectory=mediafiles&amp;mediaId=1752409&amp;fileName=graphic--31-days-of-prayer--guide-photo-0-0-290-400.jpg" width="290" height="400" alt="GRAPHIC : 31 Days of Prayer : Guide Photo - Photo of the 31 Days of..." title="GRAPHIC : 31 Days of Prayer : Guide Photo - Photo of the 31 Days of..." style="float: right;"></li><li><a href="/article/day-4-devotional-praying-for-our-senatesenators/">October 4 -&nbsp;Day 4</a></li><li><a href="/article/day-5-devotional-praying-for-our-congressrepresentatives/">October 5 -&nbsp;Day 5</a></li><li>Guest Article - Day 5</li><li><a href="/article/day-6-devotional-praying-for-our-governor/">October 6 -&nbsp;Day 6</a></li><li><a href="/article/day-7-devotional-praying-for-our-state-supreme-court/">October 7 -&nbsp;Day 7</a></li><li><a href="/article/day-8-devotional-praying-for-our-state-senators/">October 8 -&nbsp;Day 8</a></li><li><a href="/article/day-9-devotional-praying-for-our-state-representatives/">October 9 -&nbsp;Day 9</a></li><li><a href="/article/day-10-devotional-praying-for-our-mayor/">October 10 -&nbsp;Day 10</a></li><li><a href="/article/day-11-devotional-praying-for-our-citytown-council/">October 11 -&nbsp;Day 11</a></li><li><a href="/article/day-12-devotional-praying-for-our-military/">October 12 -&nbsp;Day 12</a></li><li><a href="/article/day-13-devotional-praying-for-our-firemenparamedi